{
  "id": "019d333d-c4d0-7923-8723-8fce481bde60",
  "content": "# Spoke CLI Design (2026-03-28)\n\nDetailed design for `corvia workspace spoke` subcommand group.\n\n## Commands\n- `spoke create --repo <name> --issue <N>` - spawn spoke container with Docker, clone repo, start Claude Code\n- `spoke list` - query Docker for containers with `corvia.spoke=true` label\n- `spoke logs <name>` - stream spoke container logs\n- `spoke destroy <name>` - stop and remove spoke container\n\n## Key Architecture\n- HubContext: resolves Docker-from-Docker host paths via `docker inspect $(hostname)`\n- SpokeProvisioner: extends existing DockerProvisioner in corvia-kernel\n- State tracked via Docker labels (stateless, no files)\n- Agent identity via CORVIA_AGENT_ID env var (unique per spoke)\n- Auth via host-path mount of .credentials.json (read-only)\n- Network via hub's Docker compose network (auto-detected)\n\n## Config\n`[workspace.spokes]` section in corvia.toml: image, network, auth_mode\n\n## Implementation: 9 tasks across corvia-common, corvia-kernel, corvia-cli\nDoc: docs/decisions/2026-03-28-spoke-cli-design.md",
  "source_version": "mcp",
